ment between sessions and choosing appropriate strengths minimises gum impact. No studies have linked nicotine pouch use to periodontal disease or permanent gum damage."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How do nicotine pouches compare to snus?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Nicotine pouches contain no tobacco leaf, while snus contains ground tobacco. This means pouches have significantly lower levels of tobacco-specific nitrosamines (TSNAs). Both deliver nicotine through oral absorption. Swedish snus has a strong epidemiological safety record spanning decades, and nicotine pouches remove the remaining tobacco-related risk factors. Pouches also produce no staining and less odour."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is nicotine itself dangerous?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Nicotine is a stimulant that raises heart rate and blood pressure temporarily. It is addictive. However, nicotine alone is not responsible for the serious diseases caused by smoking—those come from tar, carbon monoxide, and thousands of combustion chemicals. The Royal College of Physicians and Public Health England have stated that nicotine itself, while not risk-free, poses a relatively low health risk when separated from tobacco smoke."}}]})} />

